    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Single or multiple leaves of a book that contain errors or defects and are replaced by a corrected leaf, leaves, or slip. Distinguished from "cancellans", the leaf or leaves used to replace the removed cancellandum.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een of verscheidene bladen van een boek die fouten of gebreken vertonen en worden vervangen door een gecorrigeerde vellen of stroken. Te onderscheiden van  'verbeterbladen', het blad of de bladen die worden gebruikt om het verwijderde cancellandum te vervangen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>單張或多張有錯誤或瑕疵的紙頁，由正確的紙頁取代。不同於「替代頁」，替代頁是用來取代已經移除的錯誤頁。 </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
